ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[AFSSA -- the French Agency for Food Safety -- was established in April
1999 under 3 ministries. The 2 main responsibilities of the agency are an
assessment function covering the whole food chain, and scientific and
technical support functions. The Agency maintains strong scientific
components, which include a Scientific Council, Specialist Expert
Committees and Specialist Scientific Committees. The first proposal of
AFSSA to extend the list of sheep and goats SRMs, as mentioned in the
posting, can be seen in the Agency's web-site:
<http://www.afssa.fr/ftp/basedoc/avisovinsgb.pdf>
France's concern about the theoretical possibility of BSE entering the
sheep industry and "mimicking" scrapie can be understood in light of the
epizootiological situation there. France reported to the OIE 56 scrapie
outbreaks in 1999 and 53 in 2000, exceeded only by the UK -- 181 and 156
outbreaks, respectively. - Mod.AS
